-------> Behaviour: Fellowship.

Ive been asking Christians for their thoughts about the 3 most important Christian behaviours

Time with God through prayer, time reading the bible to understand the word and fellowship all some up as the big 3

Weve covered the first two already so today we're talking about fellowship

Seems fitting considering this is a fellowship service

Specifically, 3 questions I want to answer:

1. Why is fellowship important?
2. How do we achieve fellowship?
3. What is fellowship?


Start with the idea of vertical fellowship and horizontal fellowship

Vertical fellowship is with God

Horizontal fellowship is with fellow Christians and also with non Christians

The only thing we can bring to heaven is other people. Heard this and it hit me hard

Fellowship with Christians allows us to support and be supported by other believers in our quest for living Biblically. Not an easy endeavour in a sinful world

Fellowship with non Christians is our outlet to spread the gospel and help others come to Jesus and live righteously


Fellowship is deeper than just social interaction

It's a deep spiritual partnership consisting of sharing and joint participation

Sharing meals. Sharing time. Sharing resources. Sharing life stories. Sharing struggles

Sharing in life means involving others in our lived experience and being part of the experience of others. Being present and available to serve when needed

This fellowship service offers spiritual accountability. Becoming a fellow means comitting to being here every week for an hour and building meaningful connections with other fellows

The Greek word for fellowship is Koinonia meaning communion, joint participation, partnership and intimacy

Shared life is a bond that unites Christians with one another and with Jesus Christ

Felowship isn't passive. It's active. It involves doing things together actively to forward the kingdom

Prayer and encouragement

Participation within a community

Our hope is that while we all have a home church where we worship, a digital fellowship can endure and become a source of community even when we move physical locations and find a different church

Enduring fellowship

Christian fellowship offers us connection and relationship between Christians that cannot be had with non Christians. 

Come together in fellowship to teach each other things. Teach things about health, money, communicating the gospel, ways of living etc

Fellowship is a means of perseverance to maintain faith until then end. Fellowship offers social support to grow our faith and expand our capacity to communicate and spread the gospel

A weekly bible study practice to deepen our understanding of scripture

Experiencing life together and building each other up



-------> Stewardship: Properties of money

Last week we talked about food. Eat what God provides with thanksgiving. Natural food. Fruit roll ups arent made by God. Most products in the grocery store isnt food made by God. Beware of them

This week we're talking about money, specically the properties of money. 

Why? Because storing your time in bad currency is not good stewardship

Not only does storing your time in sinful currency steal your time, it makes you participate in a system of theft that doesn't please God

Saving in righteous money called bitcoin is both wise (because it protects and preserves your time) and also pleases God because it's an honest measure. 

Covering the properties of money allows you to understand what differentiates good vs bad money which is really important to reclaim finanncial sovereignty and escape sinful currency that steals from you







